00:22:17,630 --> 00:22:19,380
I said no!

245
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:21,930
Ahjussi! Ahjussi!

246
00:22:22,860 --> 00:22:24,350
I'm telling you I can do a good job, Ahjussi.

247
00:22:24,350 --> 00:22:28,940
Hey! Even strong men can't handle a week of this work and quit.

248
00:22:28,940 --> 00:22:33,200
How would a young woman do it? There's no way.

249
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:38,770
I'm extremely thankful that you're calling me miss, but I'm not just any Miss. I'm a miss who does weightlifting!

250
00:22:38,770 --> 00:22:41,580
I'm telling you that I can lift 100kg!

251
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,380
- Weightlifter? 
 - Yes.

252
00:22:44,380 --> 00:22:45,800
Really?

253
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,770
I even won first in a recent competition. Do you want me to show you the article?

254
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:53,960
No, no even then you can't work here. That's just sports. This is real work. You can't compare those two.

255
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:56,170
You can't even do it even with a very strong back strength.

256
00:22:56,170 --> 00:22:59,270
- Aw man.  
 - Manager, can you get these— 

257
00:22:59,270 --> 00:23:01,680
Can I put these over there, Ajusshi?

258
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:05,310
Aigoo. It's heavy! Very heavy.

259
00:23:05,310 --> 00:23:07,860
Ah what do you mean it's heavy? It's so light!

260
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:11,080
This? This too?

261
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:17,000
Aigoo. This is so heavy. This must be the heavy one. This is heavy.

262
00:23:26,340 --> 00:23:29,520
Okay. Just a moment.

263
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,860
Ah, I told her I'd play with her.

264
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:42,460
Why isn't she answering again?

265
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:46,130
Is she sleeping?

266
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:51,310
Bok Joo!
 Hyung Jae Yi 

267
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,620
Yes, Hyung.

268
00:23:58,890 --> 00:24:04,820
Here. I ran here because I didn't want it to cool. What's up?

269
00:24:06,690 --> 00:24:09,940
Ah, I was just on the way to Ah Yeong and thought you'd be in the swimming pool.

270
00:24:09,940 --> 00:24:12,160
Are you going to eat dinner with Doc?

271
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,690
We'll see.

272
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:18,780
In any case, you are quite the player, playing with girls' hearts as you please.

273
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:25,830
Well, I can't deny it since I've sinned, but I feel like I've been wronged.

274
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:28,430
And my life's motto was to live without doing bad things.

275
00:24:28,430 --> 00:24:34,150
That's why it's worse. If you were a straight-up bad person, I could curse at you.

276
00:24:34,150 --> 00:24:36,220
Oh, really, rascal.

277
00:24:36,220 --> 00:24:41,210
So how is Bok Joo doing these days?. Is she doing well?

278
00:24:41,210 --> 00:24:42,590
Why are you asking that?

279
00:24:42,590 --> 00:24:46,340
I can't even ask that? Of course, I'd be worried about her.

280
00:24:46,340 --> 00:24:50,220
Aigoo, forget it. Do not worry about her anymore.

281
00:24:50,220 --> 00:24:55,860
Don't have any interest! You're still in the danger zone. I'll take care of Bok Joo.

282
00:24:55,860 --> 00:24:57,760
Hey you—

283
00:24:57,760 --> 00:24:59,410
What?

284
00:25:01,850 --> 00:25:05,720
I'm right, huh? She is not just a friend, is she?

285
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,750
You like her, don't you?

286
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:15,490
I don't know. I must be crazy. She is really not my style of girl.

287
00:25:15,490 --> 00:25:19,430
How can a person have a style they like? If you come to like them, you like them.

288
00:25:19,430 --> 00:25:24,770
I knew it. Whenever you guys are together, your eyes start sparkling.

289
00:25:24,770 --> 00:25:26,750
Treat her well. That friend is cute.

290
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:31,750
She's that cute, but you rejected her? You made that child cry for no reason, and you suck at picking up signals.

291
00:25:31,750 --> 00:25:35,650
You should have noticed the moment she asked if you liked Messi!

292
00:25:35,650 --> 00:25:38,790
I didn't know that was what it meant.

293
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:44,200
So, when are you going to confess?

294
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:50,830
I'll wait and see. I don't think it's the right time yet. She's been in a slump lately.

295
00:25:50,830 --> 00:25:51,660
Ah, okay.

296
00:25:51,660 --> 00:25:57,350
She took a break from sports too. I should just watch over her from the side while she gets over it, and wait for the proper time.

297
00:25:57,350 --> 00:26:03,080
Ah, you're not kidding around. And who said you weren't my brother?

298
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:04,370
You really like her.

299
00:26:04,370 --> 00:26:06,990
Of course. Why would I be faking?

300
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:14,250
Hyung, if you make her cry one more time, just watch. I'm going to just—

301
00:26:15,490 --> 00:26:19,450
How frightening, do you plan on hitting your brother?

302
00:26:19,450 --> 00:26:22,810
Well... I won't hit you.

303
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:28,830
Oh, what do you mean, congratulations? I'll get loads of work.

304
00:26:28,830 --> 00:26:31,200
You know there is a lot of work needing to be done in the Association, don't you? Yes.

305
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:35,720
Unni, when our professor becomes a director of the Association, will we get some benefits from it?

306
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,180
Will it be advantageous for us in the competition?

307
00:26:37,180 --> 00:26:41,300
Oh, well... It wouldn't be bad.

308
00:26:43,950 --> 00:26:45,560
Is she sleeping right now?

309
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:49,610
What's wrong with her lately? Her dark circles have reached down to here.

310
00:26:54,210 --> 00:26:54,900
Enjoy it.

311
00:26:54,900 --> 00:26:57,120
Yes, thank you.

312
00:26:57,120 --> 00:27:00,500
I said that I was going to buy you something delicious, but it's only rice soup? I tried to buy you something expensive.

313
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:02,900
I've been in the mood for their rice soup since a few days ago.

314
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:04,800
This place used to be our go-to restaurant during our college days.

315
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:09,260
We used to eat this one until we were sick of it. But nothing has changed in this place.

316
00:27:09,260 --> 00:27:13,100
What's to change about this place? Only people change.

317
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:15,700
By the way, Sunbae Sang Go didn't come after all.

318
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:17,710
It's said he had something come up suddenly or something.

319
00:27:17,710 --> 00:27:20,390
I tried to spy on whether he lives well or not.

320
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:23,020
Is that so?

321
00:27:23,020 --> 00:27:28,180
Oh, by the way. Joon Hyeong and Bok Joo. Has there been any progress in their relationship since then?

322
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:31,030
I'm not sure.

323
00:27:31,030 --> 00:27:33,360
I'd really like for them to work out well.

324
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:38,060
From what I see, rather than a girl who's like a fox, someone like Bok Joo is perfect for Joon Hyeong.

325
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:41,830
First off she has a great personality, like me.

326
00:27:43,090 --> 00:27:46,060
That's what you ultimately wanted to say, right?

327
00:27:47,060 --> 00:27:49,470
I also hope those two work out well.

328
00:27:51,050 --> 00:27:52,930
Hey, Hyung.

329
00:27:52,930 --> 00:27:59,070
Hey, Hyung. There are no deliveries or anything so let's just close up for today.  Our mood's not the best either.

330
00:27:59,070 --> 00:28:05,570
This damned wench. Seriously, even my mood is going down because of that rascal Bok Joo.

331
00:28:05,570 --> 00:28:08,210
But, say ...

332
00:28:08,210 --> 00:28:12,820
I think it'll be good for me to raise my mood by playing some billiards or something.

333
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:28,660
Aigoo, our future nephew-in-law. You came?

334
00:28:28,660 --> 00:28:29,740
Hello.

335
00:28:29,740 --> 00:28:32,290
Well, our household is not exactly in a "hello" kind of mood.

336
00:28:32,290 --> 00:28:34,600
Is Bok Joo possibly inside? She's not answering her phone.

337
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:35,790
Bok Joo isn't home.

338
00:28:35,790 --> 00:28:36,480
What?

339
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:40,070
She's at her part time job. She called to say she'd be late.

340
00:28:40,070 --> 00:28:41,610
Part time?

341
00:28:58,620 --> 00:29:02,580
You're really impressive. There's something different about a weightlifter after all.

342
00:29:02,580 --> 00:29:07,440
Well, I've been lifting heavy things ever since I was younger. Something like this is just like a feather.

343
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:11,160
This is really your vocation. Let's take this as our permanent job.

344
00:29:11,910 --> 00:29:14,400
Since the supervisor left, we can go too.

345
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,020
Yes, Oppa.

346
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:19,720
You must be hungry after using up all that energy.

347
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:22,990
Yes. I  was already hungry, not even an hour after eating dinner.

348
00:29:22,990 --> 00:29:27,770
Would you like to eat a bowl of noodles at the stand in front of this place? I'll treat you for your getting a job here.

349
00:29:27,770 --> 00:29:29,750
Really? Can I eat two?

350
00:29:29,750 --> 00:29:34,140
Ah, Oppa has a lot of money. I'll even buy you some dumplings.

351
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:36,140
Oh, you're playing hard!

352
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:37,950
Kim Bok Joo!

353
00:29:41,090 --> 00:29:43,360
Jeong Joon Hyeong, what are you doing here?

354
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:47,030
What do you mean? I'm here to see you.

355
00:29:47,030 --> 00:29:48,890
How did you know about this place?

356
00:29:48,890 --> 00:29:53,700
I went to your place to eat chicken and your uncle told me.

357
00:30:00,210 --> 00:30:04,260
I'm sorry, but since my friend's here, maybe we can eat noodles next time.

358
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:07,260
Then your friend can join us.

359
00:30:08,370 --> 00:30:10,960
I have an allergy to noodles

360
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:15,280
You can eat something else. Over there, the tender bones dish is famous. The lady is very good at cooking that dish.

361
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,150
Tender bones dish?

362
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:20,220
Whenever I eat with someone unfamiliar,

363
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:23,340
I get slight social phobia and use violence.

364
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:25,900
I  curse  a bit too.

365
00:30:27,780 --> 00:30:29,210
Hey!

366
00:30:36,060 --> 00:30:40,940
Um, my friend is a bit sick.

367
00:30:44,090 --> 00:30:46,120
Then I'll be heading out first. See you tomorrow.

368
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:49,060
Let's eat noodles together next time, Oppa.

369
00:30:55,950 --> 00:30:59,010
You're going through so much at such a young age. Cheer up.

370
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:04,430
Hey, what's wrong with you? Are you really allergic to noodles?

371
00:31:04,430 --> 00:31:08,300
Sometimes, when I'm not in good condition.

372
00:31:08,300 --> 00:31:10,140
Let's go.

373
00:31:12,570 --> 00:31:14,570
Yeah.

374
00:31:14,570 --> 00:31:20,660
♬   I don't want a lot for Christmas. There is just one thing I need   ♬

375
00:31:20,660 --> 00:31:25,280
Aish!

376
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:28,740
It's because you're in such a rush. Here.

377
00:31:28,740 --> 00:31:32,950
But, what's with that slimy looking man from before? Is he a regular employee there?

378
00:31:32,950 --> 00:31:36,240
Oh, that oppa.

379
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:40,450
He's working part-time while on break from school. He treats me so well because I'm like his younger sister.

380
00:31:40,450 --> 00:31:42,240
Oppa?

381
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:45,110
What oppa?! How long have you seen him that you're already calling him oppa?!

382
00:31:45,110 --> 00:31:48,720
You! Don't go around looking clueless!

383
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:53,180
Hey, you have to be wary of all men aside from your father and uncle.

384
00:31:53,180 --> 00:31:56,970
Then what about you? Do I have to be wary of you too? You're a man.

385
00:31:56,970 --> 00:32:01,340
Me... Take me out of that list.

386
00:32:01,340 --> 00:32:03,400
What is he saying?

387
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:06,230
How's your part-time job? Is it okay?

388
00:32:06,230 --> 00:32:09,730
I heard that it's a job that even most men find difficult.

389
00:32:09,730 --> 00:32:13,490
It is hard. It's different from lifting weights,

390
00:32:13,490 --> 00:32:19,310
but it's manageable. After working for a short period of time, I sweat so much

391
00:32:19,310 --> 00:32:26,780
but when I drink a cup of sweet instant coffee during my break, the feeling is killer.

392
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:29,820
If someone saw you, they would think that you've done manual labor for years now.

393
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:36,170
To be honest, I'm telling this to just you, but I'm going to learn piano with the money I earn from the job.

394
00:32:36,170 --> 00:32:40,570
Piano? What? It's not the cello, but the piano?

395
00:32:40,570 --> 00:32:44,360
I just chose the cello back then because I saw a cello decoration on his desk.

396
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:46,880
Since I was young, playing the piano was my fantasy.

397
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:52,280
All of the girls in my class could play "Butterfly" on the piano, I was the only one who couldn't. Ever since I can remember, I only trained.

398
00:32:52,280 --> 00:32:57,430
Because of my indomitable mind, I want to learn to play it too. But I think it'll be too hard,

399
00:32:57,430 --> 00:33:00,170
and the instruction fee is much more expensive than the piano.

400
00:33:00,170 --> 00:33:03,790
Ah! Anyway, I'm so excited!

401
00:33:03,790 --> 00:33:06,110
Do, Re, Mi, Do, Re, Mi...

402
00:33:07,420 --> 00:33:10,520
It'll suit you well. Your fingers are long too.

403
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:14,400
Hey, I'll play the piano at your wedding.

404
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:18,200
I'll decline. You're going to ruin my wedding.

405
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:22,280
Instead, you can stand next to me.

406
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:25,510
Are you crazy? Your bride has to stand next to you, why would I stand there?!

407
00:33:25,510 --> 00:33:29,210
Fine! I won't stand you next to me! Don't stand next to me!

408
00:33:29,210 --> 00:33:32,540
Just eat!

409
00:33:32,540 --> 00:33:37,740
Hey, and don't talk to that slimy salamander. It makes me feel bad.

410
00:33:37,740 --> 00:33:40,710
Hey, wasn't that oppa kind of handsome?

411
00:33:43,380 --> 00:33:47,020
Here. Now, let's listen to your story.

412
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:49,170
What have you been doing lately?

413
00:33:49,170 --> 00:33:53,490
I've just been helping out my older sister. She runs a hair salon in front of  Jung Ang University.

414
00:33:53,490 --> 00:33:55,340
Scissor-hands?

415
00:33:56,270 --> 00:33:59,720
Does it match your aptitude?

416
00:34:01,090 --> 00:34:05,400
What aptitude? I'm just taking small side-jobs.

417
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:09,690
Hey, let's drink at the same pace.

418
00:34:11,660 --> 00:34:13,760
Thank you.

419
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,550
Here, here.

420
00:34:18,650 --> 00:34:21,870
Um, a-are you okay? Do you think you can walk? Huh?

421
00:34:22,780 --> 00:34:26,150
Yes...ugh...

422
00:34:26,150 --> 00:34:28,690
Let go.

423
00:34:30,930 --> 00:34:33,580
Here,

424
00:34:33,580 --> 00:34:35,440
get on my back.

425
00:34:37,010 --> 00:34:38,850
Why are you being good to me?

426
00:34:38,850 --> 00:34:41,830
How am I good to you?

427
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:45,560
What's the big deal about lending you my back? Now, come on.

428
00:34:49,680 --> 00:34:51,390
Um...

429
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:55,890
Uncle, do you like me?

430
00:34:55,890 --> 00:34:58,850
This old woman, seriously.

431
00:35:00,420 --> 00:35:05,410
I mean, old women like you—

432
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,220
I do like you.

433
00:35:11,010 --> 00:35:14,480
I like you. Why? Can't I like you?

434
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:19,580
No, that's possible. A human likes another human.

435
00:35:20,410 --> 00:35:22,140
Um, that...

436
00:35:22,140 --> 00:35:29,870
That one single thing that no one can ever figure out, that's love.

437
00:35:31,510 --> 00:35:33,730
Yes, fine. Fine...

438
00:35:33,730 --> 00:35:36,440
There's nothing to it, let's date.

439
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:37,530
What?

440
00:35:37,530 --> 00:35:40,410
I said let's date.

441
00:35:40,410 --> 00:35:44,950
Before I become an old wrinkly can,

442
00:35:44,950 --> 00:35:49,120
let's date! There's nothing special about it!

443
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:51,430
Are you serious?

444
00:35:51,430 --> 00:35:54,900
I mean, I mean...You're not saying this because you're drunk,

445
00:35:54,900 --> 00:35:58,180
but you're serious about this? For real?

446
00:35:58,180 --> 00:36:02,790
What? You can't trust me? Should I make you trust me?

447
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:18,850
You don't have to take me back home. I can just beat up anyone who comes onto me.

448
00:36:18,850 --> 00:36:23,680
Hey, don't act up. No matter how strong you are, you can't win against a man.

449
00:36:24,890 --> 00:36:26,520
Still? Even like this?

450
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:28,620
Hey, I take back what I said! Cancel!

451
00:36:28,620 --> 00:36:32,180
You're no match for me, yet you're acting up.

452
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:41,160
The scent of winter is nice, it's refreshing.

453
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:45,260
It's cold. I wish spring came quickly.

454
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:50,060
Joon Hyeong, I saw the doctor on the street earlier.

455
00:36:50,060 --> 00:36:51,890
Really?

456
00:36:51,890 --> 00:36:54,540
You two seem to coincidentally run into each other often.

457
00:36:54,540 --> 00:36:57,630
No, he didn't see me. I was the only one who saw him.

458
00:36:57,630 --> 00:36:59,900
So? How did it feel to see him again?

459
00:36:59,900 --> 00:37:02,800
Did your heart still tear apart to shreds?

460
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:05,320
No, not that.

461
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:07,900
It felt strange.

462
00:37:07,900 --> 00:37:13,090
The times when I attended the clinic because I was obsessing over him seem like such a long time ago.

463
00:37:13,090 --> 00:37:15,320
You know when you catch a cold

464
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:19,790
that won't go away, even if you take medicine and do all sorts of things, and when the symptoms start to ease up,

465
00:37:19,790 --> 00:37:22,870
you feel that it's the end.

466
00:37:22,870 --> 00:37:26,870
Then that means you're fine now. That's good.

467
00:37:26,870 --> 00:37:28,910
Well, I guess.

468
00:37:28,910 --> 00:37:34,090
Like you said in the past, I think time is taking care of everything.

469
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:38,700
We're here. You should leave now.

470
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:43,340
Hey, can't you take me to the front of the school? Then I'll take you back to your house again.

471
00:37:43,340 --> 00:37:47,070
What are you talking about? Hurry up and leave. I have to work overtime tomorrow so I have to rest today.

472
00:37:47,070 --> 00:37:49,530
What? You work overtime too?

473
00:37:49,530 --> 00:37:52,270
Yeah. They said that they have a lot of work tomorrow so I should work overtime.

474
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:55,280
How can they order a part-timer to work overtime?

475
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:57,140
- Then you'll end in the middle of the night.
 - Yeah.

476
00:37:57,140 --> 00:38:00,580
It's fine. If I work together with that oppa from before, I'll finish quickly.

477
00:38:00,580 --> 00:38:01,760
Oppa?

478
00:38:01,760 --> 00:38:03,070
Leave.

479
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:05,990
